"{\"uid\": \"rnz.co.nz-news-olympics-2024-523997-paris-2024-why-do-olympic-champions-bite-their-medals\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Gymnast Simone Biles takes a chomp out of her latest gold medal.Photo:AFP/LOIC VENANCE  There are a few things you can expect to see at each Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 155, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8, \"end\": 20, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thegymnastics GOAT Simone Bilesexecuting a death-defying move is one.\", \"from\": 157, \"to\": 226, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TheBlack Ferns Sevens annihilating their competitionis another.\", \"from\": 227, \"to\": 290, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But one sight raises more questions than answers: That of winners biting their medals while on the podium.\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 398, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's why they do it.\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 422, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"New Zealand rowers Ollie Maclean, Logan Ullrich, Tom Murray and Matt Macdonald chow down on the silver medals they won in the men's four.Photo:AFP/BERTRAND GUAY  Back in the day, gold and other precious metals were used as a form of currency.\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 424, \"end\": 435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9990690122722604, \"rank\": 0.0005199131649200679, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When a person received a lump of gold, one way to check its authenticity was to bite into it.\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold is softer than other metals, so if your teeth marks were visible, chances were good the gold was real.\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the early days of the modern Olympics, gold medals were just that - pure gold.\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, that practice stopped in 1912, according to the International Olympic Committee.\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 1043, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1011, \"end\": 1042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nowadays, medals are made of a silver compound, with a few grams of gold for the first-place winners.\", \"from\": 1045, \"to\": 1146, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This year's medals alsoeach contain a tiny piece of iron from past refurbishments of the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1250, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So if the medals are no longer pure gold, why do athletes continue to gnaw on them?\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1335, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The answer, according to the International Olympic Committee, is simple: Because photographers ask them to.\", \"from\": 1337, \"to\": 1444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1366, \"end\": 1397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"David Wallechinsky, the president of the International Society of Olympic Historians, previously told CNN the shot had become an \\\"obsession\\\" among photographers.\", \"from\": 1446, \"to\": 1607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1446, \"end\": 1464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Wallechinsky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David Wallechinsky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Wallechinsky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Wallechinsky\"}, {\"begin\": 1548, \"end\": 1551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"score\": 0.9999999669980758, \"rank\": 2.8985755910674596e-08, \"text\": \"CNN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think they look at it as an iconic shot, as something that you can probably sell,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1703, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not think it's something the athletes would probably do on their own.\\\"\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1781, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the 2010 Winter Olympics, Germany's David M\\u00f6ller broke a tooth chomping on the silver medal he won in the luge.\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1812, \"end\": 1819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.9751998551759474, \"rank\": 0.020016100499059854, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 1822, \"end\": 1834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_M\\u00f6ller\", \"score\": 0.9999908529364326, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David M\\u00f6ller\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_M\\u00f6ller\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_M\\u00f6ller\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The photographers wanted a picture of me holding the medal just with my teeth,\\\" he told the German publicationBild.\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 2015, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Later, at dinner, I noticed a bit of one of my teeth was missing.\\\"\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2084, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Injuries aside, the now-famous pose still looms large, and it's likely to be something we continue to see for years to come.\", \"from\": 2086, \"to\": 2210, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a92024,Radio New Zealand  The double sculls win in Paris marked the start of a magic hour that saw three medals for New Zealand's Olympic rowers.Audio  Sarah Hirini has explained why she looked \\\"so sad on the podium\\\" after taking a brutal knock to the face.\", \"from\": 2212, \"to\": 2478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2228, \"end\": 2245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_New_Zealand\", \"score\": 0.9994195576319027, \"rank\": 0.0005807794772096109, \"text\": \"Radio New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_New_Zealand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_New_Zealand\"}, {\"begin\": 2272, \"end\": 2277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 3.1502650062335164e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2337, \"end\": 2348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9990690122722604, \"rank\": 0.0005199131649200679, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2373, \"end\": 2385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Hirini\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sarah Hirini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Hirini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Hirini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Black Ferns Sevens have fought back to beat Canada 19-12 to defend their Olympic gold.\", \"from\": 2480, \"to\": 2570, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2528, \"end\": 2534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9159085223281299, \"rank\": 0.08635042261400978, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Medallists at the Paris Olympics will be rewarded with a piece of the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 2572, \"to\": 2655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"NZ claimed its biggest-ever medal haul in Tokyo in 2021.\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2713, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2657, \"end\": 2659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9915250464951089, \"rank\": 0.008368058714934288, \"text\": \"NZ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2699, \"end\": 2704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9973153929528475, \"rank\": 0.002689046849927285, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Can that be beaten in 2024?\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2741, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"for ad-free news and current affairs  Olympics 2024 RSS  Follow RNZ News\", \"from\": 2743, \"to\": 2815, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2795, \"end\": 2798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.